FBIS3-51464 "drlat011_a_94012" FBIS-LAT-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 CARIBBEAN U.S. Broadcasters Association Demands TV Marti Closure FL1501011294 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 2320 GMT 14 Jan 94 FL1501011294 Havana Cuba Vision Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] The U.S. National Association of Broadcasters has demanded that TV Marti, the anti-Cuban television station, be closed. The association has described the station as inefficient and illegal. In statements to a special U.S. Congressional body, created to study the future of TV Marti and Radio Marti, (William Haratuntam), adviser to the National Association of Broadcasters, said that TV Marti violates the international agreements that limit the use of radio and television signals for domestic use only. The so-called TV Marti and Radio Marti have been on the air since May 1985 and March 1990, respectively.
